<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA General Task//EN" "generalTask.dtd">
<task id="task_azc_wgy_w5">
    <title>Enabling Kerberos with Cloudera Manager</title>
    <shortdesc>To enable <ph
            conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/> to use
        Kerberos, use Cloudera Manager.</shortdesc>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p><indexterm>Cloudera Manager<indexterm>enabling
                        Kerberos</indexterm></indexterm><indexterm>Kerberos<indexterm>enabling
                        through Cloudera Manager</indexterm></indexterm>When you enable Kerberos
                through Cloudera Manager, Cloudera Manager creates the required Kerberos principal
                and keytab. </p>
            <p>The <ph
                    conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                /> configuration properties include Kerberos properties that you can ignore. </p>
        </context>
        <steps id="steps_rry_chy_w5">
            <step>
                <cmd>To enable Kerberos, in Cloudera Manager, go to the
                        <wintitle>Configuration</wintitle> page. </cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Select <uicontrol>Enable Kerberos Client</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Restart <ph
                        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                    />.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
